729352f-a.text:
Richmond Avenue, at the S.E. corner of Victory
Boulevard, showing (center of view) the ruins of the old
Bull's Head Tavern of pre-Revolutionary days. It was a
tory headquarters during the War of Independence. The view
is wrst on the south side of Victory Boulevard.
May 16, 1937
L. Sperr
